%{
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;
%}

%%
[0-9]+          { cout << "NUMBER: " << yytext << endl; }
[a-zA-Z_][a-zA-Z0-9_]* { cout << "IDENTIFIER: " << yytext << endl; }
[+\-*/=]        { cout << "OPERATOR: " << yytext << endl; }
[(){};,]        { cout << "PUNCTUATION: " << yytext << endl; }
[ \t\n]+        ;  // ignore whitespace
.               { cout << "UNKNOWN: " << yytext << endl; }
%%

int main(int argc, char **argv){
    yylex();
    return 0;
}

âœ… How to Run on Ubuntu / Linux

Save the file as token.l.

Open terminal and run:

flex token.l          # generates lex.yy.c
g++ lex.yy.c -o token -lfl   # compile with C++ and link flex library
./token                # run the program


Then type an expression like:

a = 5 + b * (c - 2);
